## Description
Calculated properties do not return values when passed into `pwsh` via the `-Command` argument.

## Steps to reproduce

- Open terminal and run the following command:

`pwsh -c "@{ items = @( Get-Process | Select -Last 5 @{n='title';e={$_.ProcessName}},@{n='subtitle';e={$_.ID}} | ? 'title' -ne '' )} | ConvertTo-Json"`

- To prove that the calculated columns are the issue, remove them and select default property names which returns values as expected.

`pwsh -c "@{ items = @( Get-Process | Select ProcessName, ID -Last 5 )} | ConvertTo-Json"`

